      By the way
   =20
 =20
The technology that AMC used to let its shareholders ask questions is from =
a firm called Say Technologies. Here=E2=80=99s  some more Say Technologies =
news from this morning:Robinhood Markets Inc. agreed to buy Say Technologie=
s, a tool for shareholder voting and communication, in its first acquisitio=
n as a public company.The approximately $140 million all-cash deal will giv=
e Robinhood access to Say=E2=80=99s software, which helps company sharehold=
ers exercise their right to vote proxies and ask questions of management, a=
ccording to a blog post Tuesday. The announcement comes less than two weeks=
 after Robinhood made its public trading debut.Makes sense.=C2=A0
